# Normalise line endings. The repo is authored with LF (the git
# index already stores LF); without this, a Windows checkout gets
# CRLF working-tree files, which makes `gofmt -l` flag every Go
# file and breaks shell scripts on Linux. Pin the text types that
# have a gate or run on Linux to LF explicitly.
* text=auto
*.go   text eol=lf
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.ts   text eol=lf
